{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffered"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A buffered channel can only be set unbuffered if the channel’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"internal buffers have been flushed. Newly created channels or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"channels which have returned "},{"code":"eof","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not require such a flush. For write-only channels, a call to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"g_io_channel_flush () is sufficient. For all other channels,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the buffers may be flushed by a call to g_io_channel_seek_position ().","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This includes the possibility of seeking with seek type ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cur"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and an offset of zero. Note that this means that socket-based"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"channels cannot be set unbuffered once they have had data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"read from them."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On unbuffered channels, it is safe to mix read and write"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calls from the new and old APIs, if this is necessary for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"maintaining old code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default state of the channel is buffered."}]}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"buffered","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:4GLib17IOChannelProtocolPAAE3set8bufferedySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib9IOChannelC","title":"set(buffered:)"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/set(buffered:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/set(buffered:)"},"abstract":[{"text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GIOChannel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into the main event loop (see [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"]). Currently,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is only partially complete.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOChannel","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"IOChannel","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannel"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"title":"MainContext","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations":{"kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"IOChannelProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/iochannelprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel/set(buffered:)":{"type":"topic","title":"set(buffered:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/set(buffered:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"tex